article_id:1401,category_name:Events,title_name:A Facility Event Revival, Trick or Treasure!, Is Now Live!,image_path:https://dragalialost.akamaized.net/attached/information/images/db8c508aa505296570fe836cfd627db0.png,message:<div>A facility event revival, Trick or Treasure!, went live <span class="local_date" data-local_date="1592546400"></span>!</div><div><img src="https://dragalialost.akamaized.net/attached/information/images/db8c508aa505296570fe836cfd627db0.png"></div><div>Fall is here, which means it&#39;s time for harvest, Halloween, and a whole lot of sweets! The centerpiece of this Halloween party is a house made of candy, and fiends are being drawn to its sugary scent! There&#39;ll be tricks, treats, and maybe even a little danger... This wild Halloween party is just getting started!</div><div><br></div><div>■Event Overview</div><div>In Trick or Treasure!, you can acquire an event-exclusive facility: the Sweet Retreat. If you play the event, you&#39;ll have the chance to build one for your Castle Grounds!</div><div><br></div><div>The Sweet Retreat increases the stats of light-attuned adventurers. It also boosts the damage that adventurers deal against enemies in event quests. Progress through the event story and level up your Sweet Retreat.</div><div><br></div><div>Adventurers can equip wyrmprints obtained from the event&#39;s Treasure Trade or as rewards to receive more snack-o&#39;-lanterns, which are used to upgrade the Sweet Retreat, from these quests. Wyrmprints are good for more than just that, though, so try to get ahold of them to get the most out of this event!</div><div><br></div><div>Please note that special effects conferred by event-specific wyrmprints do not apply if you begin a quest during the event period but complete the quest after the event period has ended.</div><div><br></div><div>■Event Duration</div><div><span class="local_date" data-local_date="1592546400"></span> to <span class="local_date" data-local_date="1593410399"></span></div><div><br></div><div>■Reward Availability Period</div><div><span class="local_date" data-local_date="1592546400"></span> to <span class="local_date" data-local_date="1594015199"></span></div><div><br></div><div>■Event-Exclusive Facility: The Sweet Retreat</div><div>This facility increases the stats of light-attuned adventures.</div><div>It also confers a special effect that lets you deal more damage to enemies in these event quests.</div><div>The strength of this effect increases as you level up the Sweet Retreat.</div><div>This effect only applies for the duration of this event.</div><div>To level up the Sweet Retreat, you&#39;ll need snack-o&#39;-lanterns, which you can find in these event quests.</div><div><br></div><div>■Upgrade Item: Snack-o&#39;-Lanterns</div><div>You can get these from the story quests, boss battle, and extra boss battle for the Trick or Treasure! facility event revival.</div><div><br></div><div>■If You Already Obtained the Sweet Retreat</div><div>If you already have the Sweet Retreat from a past event, you will receive wyrmite instead.</div><div><br></div><div>■Boss Battles</div><div>Boss battles are quests where you can face off against boss enemies that appear in the event story. Rewards vary depending on the difficulty cleared. This quest can be played either solo or co-op.</div><div><br></div><div>■Extra Boss Battles</div><div>Although the difficulty level of extra boss battles is higher than the event boss battle on Expert difficulty, the rewards are generous and the battles do not cost stamina or getherwings.</div><div>Extra boss battles occasionally appear after clearing the event boss battle on Expert difficulty.</div><div>It will disappear again after being successfully cleared. Once the conditions for the quest are met, you can unlock it repeatedly. This quest can be played either solo or co-op.</div><div><br></div><div>・Even if you clear the boss battle several times in a row using the auto-repeat feature, the extra boss battle will only become available once at most.</div><div><br></div><div>■Challenge Battles</div><div>Challenge battles are high-difficulty quests limited to solo play, and are available in Expert, Master, and Nightmare difficulties. The Expert difficulty challenge battle is unlocked after completing the event boss battle on Expert difficulty, and the Master difficulty challenge battle will unlock when you complete the Expert difficulty challenge battle. The Nightmare difficulty challenge battle will become available at <span class="local_date" data-local_date="1592805600"></span>, and you must complete the Master difficulty challenge battle to play it.</div><div>・Even if you complete the Master difficulty challenge battle, you will not be able to play the Nightmare battle until it is available.</div><div><br></div><div>These quests will have you testing your strength against waves of enemies. If you fail to reach the last wave in Expert or Master difficulty, you will still receive rewards for the ones you did clear, but in Nightmare difficulty you must complete the final wave to earn rewards.</div><div>Finally, the drop rate for rewards differs based on the difficulty.</div><div>・The drop rate for rewards in Nightmare difficulty is the same as Master difficulty.</div><div><br></div><div>Once per day when you clear Nightmare difficulty, you can get a Grand Bounty.</div><div>・The Grand Bounty you receive is randomly selected from a set of rewards.</div><div><br></div><div>■Tricker Treat Rewards</div><div>Tricker treats are event-exclusive points that can be earned by clearing event quests. Collect them to earn all kinds of rewards!</div><div><br></div><div>■Treasure Trade Rewards</div><div>You can earn jack chocolates and candy baskets by playing event quests and trade them for various rewards on the Treasure Trade menu.</div><div>What&#39;s more, in this event you&#39;ll be able to trade snack-o&#39;-lanterns, which are required to level up the Sweet Retreat event facility, for jack chocolates and candy baskets, which are only used in the Treasure Trade, and vice versa.</div><div><br></div><div>・Snack-o&#39;-lanterns obtained in the past will carry over into this Trick or Treasure! facility event revival, but you will not be able to trade them for items on the event Treasure Trade unless you participate in the event.</div><div><br></div><div>■Event Bonus</div><div>The following wyrmprints will have bonus effects during the Trick or Treasure! facility event revival.</div><div>・Plunder Pals</div><div>・Witch&#39;s Kitchen</div><div>・Of Tricks and Treats</div><div>・Silke Lends a Hand</div><div>・Pumpkin Pail</div><div>If you equip these wyrmprints and clear event quests, you&#39;ll get even more snack-o&#39;-lanterns and tricker treats.</div><div><br></div><div>You can get Plunder Pals from the event&#39;s Treasure Trade or as a tricker treat reward. Witch&#39;s Kitchen, Of Tricks and Treats, Silke Lends a Hand, and Pumpkin Pail are available in the Treasure Trade for wyrmprints.</div><div>・The amount of event bonus effect differs based on the wyrmprint and how much the wyrmprint has been unbound.</div><div><br></div><div>■Endeavors</div><div>These endeavors can only be attempted for the duration of the event. They are separated into Daily and Limited variations. By accomplishing these endeavors, you can receive various rewards.</div><div>&nbsp;</div><div>Notes:</div><div>1. You can see more details about this event by tapping Help on the event page.</div><div>2. Players must have completed up to Chapter 2 / 2-1 (Normal) of the main campaign to participate.</div><div>3. Players must have completed up to Chapter 2 / 2-1 (Normal) of the main campaign in order to play co-op.</div><div>4. If the event ends while you are playing an event quest, the quest will continue until results have been determined and you will be able to gain the rewards shown.</div><div><br></div><div>Thank you for playing Dragalia Lost.</div>,start_time:1592546400,update_time1592365079